OL,9,Fand rehabilitation, restoring
OL,10,Fopportunity for Americans to
OL,11,Fparticipate in daily life and
OL,12,Fcontribute to their communities, and
OL,13,Ftaking steps to remove sentencing
OL,14,Fdisparities for non-violent offenders,
OL,15,Fespecially those convicted of drug
OL,16,Foffences."
OL,18,FWhite House lawyers said that those
OL,19,Fpardoned for non-violent crimes, such
OL,20,Fas drug offences, have turned their
OL,21,Flives around.
