OL,6,FWhat is clemency, and why do
OL,7,Fpresidents grant it at the end of
OL,8,Ftheir terms?
OL,10,FClemency refers to the president's
OL,11,Fpower to pardon, which erases guilt
OL,12,Fand punishment, or commutes sentences.
OL,14,FThis reduces which reduces or
OL,15,Feliminates the punishment but does not
OL,16,Fexonerate the wrongdoing.
OL,18,FIt is customary for presidents to use
OL,19,Fthis power at the end of their term to
OL,20,Fforgive crimes or shorten prison terms.
